Package: dress.graph
Type: Package
Title: DRESS - A Continuous Framework for Structural Graph Refinement
Version: 0.8.3
Date: 2026-05-04
Maintainer: Eduar Castrillo Velilla <velicast@outlook.com>
Authors@R: person("Eduar", "Castrillo Velilla", role = c("aut", "cre"),
        email = "velicast@outlook.com", comment = c(ORCID =
        "0009-0005-2492-0957"))
Description: DRESS is a deterministic, parameter-free framework for
        continuous structural graph refinement. It iterates a nonlinear
        dynamical system on real-valued edge similarities and produces
        a graph fingerprint as a sorted edge-value vector once the
        iteration reaches a prescribed stopping criterion. The
        resulting fingerprint is self-contained, isomorphism-invariant
        by construction, reproducible across vertex labelings under the
        reference implementation, numerically robust in practice, and
        efficient to compute with straightforward parallelization and
        distribution.
